        "response_text": "I've analyzed the auth middleware. Here are the key issues I found:\n\n1. **Missing expiry validation** — `jwt_handler.py` calls `jwt.decode()` without checking the `exp` claim, allowing expired tokens to pass validation.\n\n2. **Hardcoded secret** — The JWT secret is hardcoded as `'secret123'` in `middleware.py:42`. This should be loaded from environment variables.\n\n3. **No refresh token logic** — The current implementation has no way to rotate tokens after expiry, forcing users to re-authenticate unnecessarily.\n\n4. **Algorithm not pinned** — `jwt.decode()` accepts `algorithms='HS256'` but doesn't reject `none` algorithm attacks.\n\nI'll now rewrite the JWT handler to fix all four issues.",
